From 02dcfc46ee8942add0a392e8520841a4c68de179 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: damoke012 <103553692+damoke012@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 23:11:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(talos): pin hostname by VM identity + kubelet
 hostname-override
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Eliminates the class of bug that caused 2026-06-17 + 2026-06-18 cascades:
list-index-driven hostname assignment that drifts when out-of-band
talosctl patches or DHCP refreshes shift IP ordering.

Changes:
  1. modules/vsphere_vm/outputs.tf — emit vm_names output
     (vsphere_virtual_machine.vm[*].name; same count.index ordering
     as ip_addresses in steady state)

  2. modules/talos/variables.tf — accept control_plane_vm_names +
     worker_vm_names; both are required and must be count.index-aligned
     with their respective IP lists

  3. modules/talos/main.tf — replace 3 hardcoded hostname template strings
     with var.{cp,worker}_vm_names[N]:
       - init                → control_plane_vm_names[0]
       - join_cp[N]          → control_plane_vm_names[N+1]
       - join_workers[N]     → worker_vm_names[N]
     Also adds machine.kubelet.extraArgs.hostname-override pinning kubelet's
     identity to the VM-name (forces consistent reporting independent of
     OS-derived hostname or DNS).

  4. deploy/terraform/main.tf — wire module.vsphere_cp.vm_names +
     module.vsphere_worker.vm_names into module.talos.

Net string-produced behavior is identical (VM names follow the same
${prefix}-${N+1} pattern they already had), so apply should be a
no-op for hostname STRINGS — but the new kubelet hostname-override
WILL push a config delta + restart kubelet on each node. That restart
is the intended fix: forces stuck/divergent kubelets to re-register
under their declared hostname. The cilium-node-reconciler CronJob
(merged 2026-06-18 PM) handles any CN drift that surfaces during the
rolling kubelet restart.

